  "prompt": "I'm sick of hearing about Trump, can I block these questions on my Quora feed?",
  "response": "Yes, you can absolutely block questions about Trump (or any topic you're tired of seeing) on your Quora feed. Here's how you can do it:\n\n**1. Muting Topics:**\n\n   *   **On the Quora Website:**\n      *   Hover over a question about Trump in your feed.\n      *   Click the three dots (ellipsis) next to the question.\n      *   Select \"Mute [Topic related to Trump]\".  (For example, it might say \"Mute Donald Trump\" or \"Mute US Politics\").\n      *   You can mute multiple related topics if needed.\n\n   *   **On the Quora App:**\n      *   Tap the three dots (ellipsis) next to a Trump-related question.\n      *   Select \"Mute [Topic related to Trump]\".\n\n**2. Downvoting/Reporting (Less Direct, But Helpful):**\n\n   *   If you see questions you believe are low quality, biased, or violate Quora's policies, you can downvote them or report them. While this won't *directly* block all Trump-related questions, it can help Quora's algorithm learn what content you find undesirable.  However, it's less effective than muting topics.\n\n**3. Manage Your Interests:**\n\n   *   Go to your Quora profile settings. There should be a section to manage your interests.  Make sure you're *not* following any topics directly related to Trump, US politics, or similar subjects if you want to reduce their appearance in your feed.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Related Topics:** You might need to mute more than just \"Donald Trump.\"  Think about other related topics like \"US Politics,\" \"American Presidency,\" \"Republican Party,\" or even specific policies associated with him.  The more thorough you are, the fewer Trump-related questions you'll see.\n\n*   **Quora's Algorithm:**  Quora's algorithm learns from your activity.  The more you ignore or mute Trump-related questions, the less likely they are to show up in your feed.\n\n*   **New Accounts/Users:** If you've recently joined Quora or haven't used it much, it might take a little time for the algorithm to learn your preferences.  Be patient and consistently mute/ignore unwanted topics.\n\n*   **No Guarantee:**  It's impossible to *completely* eliminate all mentions of a widely discussed figure like Trump.  However, by using these methods, you can significantly reduce the amount of Trump-related content you see in your Quora feed.\n\nBy using a combination of muting topics and managing your interests, you can take control of your Quora feed and focus on the topics you actually want to see. Good luck!\n",
